 000  In addition, as reported byThe South African website, new Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture,Gayton McKenzie, promised that he has a 'big surprise' for all Team SA medal winners, suggesting there could be more prize money coming their way.\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 3038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2767, \"end\": 2770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\", \"score\": 0.9634108711086189, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"R75\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\"}, {\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5045954616260668e-37, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men:Pieter Coetze (100m, 200m backstroke), Chad le Clos (100m butterfly), Matthew Sates (100m, 200m butterfly and 200m IM)  Women:Aimee Canny (200m freestyle), Kaylene Corbett (200m breaststroke), Erin Gallagher (100m butterfly), Rebecca Meder (200m IM), Tatjana Smith (100m, 200m breaststroke)  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chad le Clos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\"}, {\"begin\": 3114, \"end\": 3127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Sates\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Sates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Sates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.o